Package stincmale.ratmex.executor

Class ScheduledTaskConfig<E extends RateMeasuredEvent>

  • java.lang.Object
    • stincmale.ratmex.executor.ScheduledTaskConfig<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - A type of container with data provided to RateListener by RateMeasuringExecutorService.
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    SubmitterWorkerScheduledTaskConfig

    @Immutable
public class ScheduledTaskConfig<E extends RateMeasuredEvent>
extends java.lang.Object
    A configuration of a scheduled task.

    The default values:

    • getInitialDelay() - Duration.ZERO
    • getDuration() - Optional.empty()
    • getRateListener() - Optional.empty()

      • getDuration

        public final java.util.Optional<java.time.Duration> getDuration​()
        Specifies the amount of time after the initial delay after which a scheduled task should not be executed anymore. There is no guarantee beyond best-effort attempt to not exceed this duration.

        An empty duration means that the task will be repeatedly executed until one of the exceptional completions specified by RateMeasuringExecutorService.scheduleAtFixedRate(Runnable, Rate, ScheduledTaskConfig) occur.

      • getRateListener

        public final java.util.Optional<RateListener<? super E>> getRateListener​()
